The paper proposes online algorithms for sequential learning in the contextual multi-armed bandit setting, which is a common problem in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper also discusses the design and implementation of efficient algorithms, which suggests a focus on computer science and data structures. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Additionally, the paper discusses Lipschitz conditions, which are commonly used in control engineering and optimization, suggesting a possible fit for cs.CE (Control Engineering) or cs.IT (Information Theory).
